# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: bocrypt / cookie / encoding / base: build + crash + option bugs
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* DONE [#A] bocrypt, cookie, encoding, base: build breaks and crash bugs  :bocrypt:cookie:encoding:base:build:memory:
  RESOLUTION (2026-06-20). All four modules build clean under the strict flags.
  Validated: base 0->"0", 255->"FF", base 40-> graceful error; cookie --help
  prints usage and exits (no crash); nema does an end-to-end -from/-to
  conversion (macintosh->macintosh) and -t still means dump-table; smallcrypt
  builds and the cipher behaviour is unchanged.
  - bocrypt/smallcrypt.c: removed the dead keylength (the cipher wraps on the key
    NUL, not keylength); BSD index/rindex -> strchr/strrchr; loadkey now
    malloc(size+1) with a NULL check (was a 1-byte heap overflow when the last
    key line had no newline); qerror uses vsnprintf.
  - cookie/cookie.c: getdefaultfilenames no longer newstr()s the NIL terminator;
    the argv scan is ii<argc (was argv[argc] -> NULL deref) and --help prints a
    usage line; the selected cookie file's fopen is NULL-checked before fseek;
    loadfilenames keeps the last char when a line lacks a newline and NULL-checks
    its malloc.
  - encoding/encoding.c: the documented single-dash -from/-to now work (added
    STR_CASE3 for -f/-from/--from; the to-case is -to/--to). -t is dump-table
    only (the old -t/--to entry shadowed it). MakeTempName is bounded (snprintf)
    and escapestr bounds its writes into buffer[1024].
  - base/base.c: prints "0" for zero (the while(n>0) loop produced an empty
    string); main validates 2<=base<=36 with a clean error instead of letting
    int_to_base's assert abort.
  Full-tree review 2026-06-20 (gcc 14, strict flags). bocrypt.c and xor.c are
  clean and crypto-correct; the problems are concentrated in smallcrypt.c and in
  the cookie/encoding/base front-ends. See [[build-system]] and
  [[common-integration]].

** Build-blockers (-Werror)

*** [critical] bocrypt/smallcrypt.c:140,211 — 'keylength' set but not used
=keylength=(int)strlen(key)= computed but never read in both =encrypt()= and
=decrypt()=. Crypto note: the cipher loop wraps via =key[keyindex]=='\0'=
(lines 195/264), so the key IS applied correctly — =keylength= is genuinely dead
code. Fix: delete it (or use it for the wrap test).

*** [critical] bocrypt/smallcrypt.c:120,125,127,132,153,155,164,298 — index/rindex implicitly declared
BSD =index=/=rindex= are not in =<string.h>= and absent under strict std.
Fix: =#include <strings.h>= with =_DEFAULT_SOURCE=, or use =strchr=/=strrchr=.

** Crash bugs (latent; cookie.c compiles clean)

*** [high] cookie/cookie.c:158 — off-by-one reads argv[argc] (NULL) -> segfault
=for(ii=1;ii<=argc;ii++)= then =strcmp(argv[ii],"--help")=; at =ii==argc=,
=argv[argc]= is NULL. Crashes whenever any argument is passed (and the loop body
is empty -- =--help= does nothing). Fix: =ii<argc=.

*** [high] cookie/cookie.c:88 — getdefaultfilenames derefs the NIL terminator
=do{i++;loadedfiles[i]=newstr(defaultfiles[i]);}while(defaultfiles[i]!=NIL);=
calls =newstr(NIL)= -> =strlen(NULL)= on the terminator before the test. Hit on
the fallback path when the cookie table can't be opened. Fix: test before copy.

*** [high] cookie/cookie.c:195 — fopen result used unchecked at fseek (:198)
The selection loop can land on a file that failed to open; =fd= is dereferenced
by =fseek= with no NULL check. Fix: check =fd=.

*** [high] bocrypt/smallcrypt.c:99 — loadkey: unchecked malloc + 1-byte heap overflow
=key=malloc((unsigned)size)= used at =key[0]='\0'= with no NULL check (OOM / empty
key file). The buffer is =size= bytes but if the last line lacks a trailing
newline the assembled string is =size+1= bytes -> one-byte heap overflow.
Fix: =malloc(size+1)= and check NULL.

** Option-parsing / logic bugs

*** [high] encoding/encoding.c:438 vs 479 — -t/-to collision; -from/-to don't work
=STR_CASE("-t")= (dump-table) precedes =STR_CASE2("-t","--to")= in the same
else-if chain, so =-t= can never mean "to". With =STR_CASE2("-f","--from")= (no
=-from=), the documented =-from code -to code= invocation is fully broken: =-from=
errors and =-to= is swallowed as dump-table. Fix: rename the conflicting short
option and add a =-from= alias.

*** [medium] base/base.c:109 — n==0 prints empty string instead of "0"
=while(n>0)= never runs for zero. Fix: special-case 0 or use do/while.

*** [medium] base/base.c:51 — invalid base aborts via assert (SIGABRT on user input)
=base=atoi(argv[2])=; values 0, 1, >36 or non-numeric trip =assert= instead of a
clean error. Fix: validate and print a usage message.

** Lower-risk

*** [medium] bocrypt/smallcrypt.c:55 — qerror() vsprintf into fixed message[BUFSIZ]
Caller formats may include filenames; overflowable. Fix: =vsnprintf=.

*** [low] encoding.c:362 / :168 — sprintf into buffer[1024] / MakeTempName strcat
=escapestr= can emit up to 4 bytes/char into 1024 unbounded; =MakeTempName=
strcats =.nema= onto =TempName[256]= from argv paths. Fix: bound both.

*** [low] cookie.c:117 — last char truncated when a line lacks a trailing newline
=malloc(l)= + forced =loadedfiles[i][l-1]='\0'= assumes a trailing =\n=.

** common / benlib integration
encoding.c uses =BenEncodingTableNamed=/=Names=, =BenApproximationTableNamed=/
=Names=, =BenBuildConversionTable= -- all match the installed Bencoding.h. It does
NOT call the recently-fixed =BenConvertString= (it rolls its own =ConvertEncoding=
at :280, indexing with 0..255 =fgetc= values), so it is not exposed to the old
signed-char bug. (encoding.c also uses =bjstring.h=/=bjarray.h=/
=bjobject_initialize= from =bjlib=; the module Makefile already carries the bjlib
-I and -l paths, so it links correctly.)

** Health
smallcrypt.c is the problem child (build-blockers + loadkey overflow + unbounded
vsprintf); cookie.c compiles but has three crash bugs; encoding.c uses benlib
correctly but its -from/-to parsing is broken; base.c is clean but mishandles 0 and aborts on invalid bases.
